arts.ttl: Everton prevail at Ipswich for first away win of the season
arts.sum: The Toffees showed little sign of rustiness after the international break, as first-half goals from Iliman Ndiaye and Michael Keane set them on course for their second league victory of the season. Everton stretched their Premier League unbeaten run to four matches as Sean Dyche ’s side saw off Ipswich Town 2-0 at Portman Road.
